Dear all,
I find that the offJacobian of aux variable '_v(coupledValue("v")),' needs to be defined in PorousFlowHeatMassTransfer.C see bold in below.
Real
PorousFlowHeatMassTransfer::computeQpResidual()
{
return _coef_var[_qp] * (_u[_qp] - _v[_qp]) * _test[_i][_qp];
}
Real
PorousFlowHeatMassTransfer::jac(unsigned int jvar) const
{
if (jvar == _var.number())
return _coef_var[_qp] * _phi[_j][_qp] * _test[_i][_qp];
else if (jvar == _v_var)
return -_coef_var[_qp] * _phi[_j][_qp] * _test[_i][_qp];
return 0.0;
}
So now if I set v as an aux variable and equals to a constant value in the input file. Do I still need the OffJacobian calculation with respect to v as shown above? And why?
Thanks for your help.
B

